President Donald J. Trump has designated all funding and contributions from foreign governments, as outlined in the Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2018, for Overseas Contingency Operations/Global War on Terrorism. This action is in accordance with section 6 of the Act and section 251(b)(2)(A) of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act of 1985. The details of this action can be found in the enclosed memorandum from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.